🔁 Duplicate Entry Validation

📌 Overview
Implemented duplicate checking to prevent multiple employees from having the same email or phone number, ensuring data integrity and consistency.

🚫 Problem

Initially, the API allowed:

Same email to be inserted multiple times
Same phone number to be reused

This could lead to data redundancy and inconsistency.

✅ Solution Implemented
🔥 Service-Level Validation

Before inserting a new employee, the system checks if an employee already exists with the same email or phone number.

var existing = _repo.GetAll()
    .FirstOrDefault(e => e.Mail == dto.Email || e.Phone == dto.Phone);

if (existing != null)
{
    throw new ArgumentException("Employee with same email or phone already exists");
}
🛡️ Optional Database-Level Protection

To ensure strict uniqueness, database constraints can also be applied:

[Index(nameof(Mail), IsUnique = true)]
[Index(nameof(Phone), IsUnique = true)]
